==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pignoration
<hw>Pig`no*ra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>pignoratio</ets>, L. <ets>pigneratio</ets>, fr.
<ets>pignerate</ets> to pledge, fr. <ets>pignus</ets>, gen.
<ets>-ous</ets> and <ets>-eris</ets>, a pledge, a pawn: cf. F.
<ets>pignoration</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of pledging or
pawning.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Civil Law)</fld> <def>The taking of cattle doing
damage, by way of pledge, till satisfaction is made.</def>
<rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pignorative</ent>⟦br⟧
